node.statement: Define the O-slice cells. For the O-admissible family F_O, the O-slice cells of dimension n are SC_O(n) = {G_+ smash_H S^{m*rho_H} : H in F_O, m*|H| = n, m >= 0}, where rho_H is the regular representation of H. These restrict the standard HHR slice cells to orbits G/H with H in F_O. Verify these are compact objects in Sp^G.
